article.headline: Cent. Arkansas 63, Texas St. 21
article.story: CONWAY, Ark. (AP) -- Nathan Brown threw for 313 yards and seven touchdowns to lead Central Arkansas over Texas State 63-21 Thursday night. Brown threw six of his TDs in the first half to help the Bears (3-3, 2-1 Southland Conference) roll to a 42-14 halftime advantage. Marquez Branson caught four passes for 80 yards and three touchdowns. Brown finished 16-of-20, and backup Robbie Park added a touchdown pass in the third quarter. Central Arkansas led 63-14 before going scoreless in the fourth. The Bears had 34 first downs, 662 yards of offense and punted only once. Leonard Ceaser ran for 113 yards and a touchdown. Texas State (1-5, 0-2) actually scored first on a 26-yard pass from Bradley George to Alvin Canady, but Central Arkansas answered with five straight touchdowns. George went 13-of-23 for 106 yards and a touchdown, and Clint Toon threw a 10-yard touchdown pass to Morris Crosby in the fourth quarter for Texas State.
